A Mana Void leeches all the mana from every ranged spell caster and healer, storing the mana within itself. Destroying the Mana Void evenly returns the total of the leeched mana via Mana Diffusion to players within $105539A1 yards.

Yor'sahj sears the blood of three random players, inflicting a base of $%105033s1 Fire damage. The further the target stands from Yor'sahj, the greater shock received from the blast.$[!4,6

In 25 player raids, Yor'sahj sears the blood of eight random players.$]
Digestive Acid periodically secretes from the stomach lining, inflicting $%105573s1 Nature damage to a player and nearby allies within $105573A1 yards.

Yor'sahj's Deep Corruption spreads to every player, causing every fifth healing or absorption effect cast on a player to trigger a violent detonation, inflicting $%105173s1 Shadow damage to all players.

When the Void collides with a player it diffuses, inflicting $%103527s1 Shadow damage split evenly between nearby players. The force of this diffusion causes the void to ricochet in the opposite direction, and the absorbed souls increase the damage the Void inflicts by $106836s1% per diffusion.

Four equidistant lines of ice extend out from Hagara and sweep across the platform. The Ice Wave inflicts $%105314s1 Frost damage on any player caught by its movement and increases their Frost damage taken by $105314s2% for $105314d.
Snowpacked Icicles fall around the edge of the platform. Where the Icicle impacts the ground, it inflicts 100000 Frost damage and knocks back any nearby players within $69425A1 yards.

Hagara places a Frostflake on a random player, reducing their movement speed by $109325s1% and an additional $109325s1% every $109325t2 sec for $109325d. When the Frostflake effect expires, it deals damage equal to $109337s2% of the player's maximum health, and creates a 10 yard radius area of frost underneath that player. The frost reduces any player's movement speed standing within the area by $109337s1%.
The feedback from the overloaded Crystal Conductors and destroyed Binding Crystals stuns Hagara and increases her damage taken by $108934s1% for $108934d.

A Crystal Conductor charged by the death of a Bound Lightning Elemental casts Lightning Conduit on the nearest player, inflicting $%105369s1 Nature damage every $105369t1 sec.

Lightning Conduit also connects the affected player to another player or Crystal Conductor within 10 yards.
Hagara targets the location of a random player, then after 3 seconds a pillar of lightning erupts. The lightning inflicts $%109563s1 Nature damage to all players within $109563A1 yards.

The Hour of Twilight falls upon Ultraxion's foes. Enemies caught within the Twilight Realm take $%103327s1 unresistable Shadow damage. Players within the normal realm forcibly enter the Twilight Realm.
The Aspects provide limited aid to the players as they fight Ultraxion.

A Corrupting Parasite inflicts increasing Shadow damage periodically. When Corrupting Parasite's duration ends, the parasite detaches from the player and causes a Parasitic Backlash. This inflicts $%108787s1 Fire damage to players within $108787A1 yards of the host.
After the Corrupting Parasite's duration ends, the parasite detaches from the host.
The Corrupting Parasite casts Unstable Corruption, inflicting $108813s1% of the Corrupted Parasite's health as Fire damage to all players.
Deathwing begins to Hemorrhage, creating several Congealing Blood at a nearby location. The Blood then moves towards Deathwing.
If a Congealing Blood reaches Deathwing, it heals him for $109102s1% of his maximum health.
Goriona unleashes a torrent of dark flame, inflicting $110212s1 Shadow damage in a $110212a1 yard cone in front of the caster.

Goriona envelops an enemy target in twilight energy, absorbing the next $110214s1 healing received. When Consuming Shroud absorbs incoming healing, unleashed energy will deal damage equal to the healing absorbed to all allies. Dying while afflicted by Consuming Shroud will release all remaining energy at once.

As the Skyfire takes damage, destructive fires break out on the ship and spread rapidly across its deck. Crewmembers rush to extinguish these blazes and keep them in check. Any player standing within a fire suffers $110095s1 Fire damage per second.
Goriona periodically unleashes a vicious barrage of fireballs that slam into the side of the Skyfire, causing the ship to suffer damage equal to $110153s1% of its remaining structural integrity.
The Flail of Go'rath spews sludge at a random player, inflicting $%110297s1 Shadow damage.

Residual Twilight effects cause all threat against Ultraxion to be reset. In addition, no threat will be generated for $105927d.$[!5,6

In Heroic Difficulty, players take $105927s2% more Physical damage for $105927d, instead of generating no threat.$]
When severely injured, Warmaster Blackhorn drains health directly from Goriona. The health drain inflicts damage equal to $110312s1% of Goriona's remaining health, and heals Blackhorn accordingly.
Warlord Zon'ozz covers random players with Disrupting Shadows. The effect inflicts $%103434s1 Shadow damage every $103434t1 seconds.
Digestive Acid periodically secretes from the stomach lining, inflicting $%105573s1 Nature damage to a random player.

When the Void collides with a player it diffuses, inflicting 50,000 Shadow damage. The force of this diffusion causes the void to ricochet in the opposite direction, and the absorbed souls increase the damage the Void inflicts by 5% per diffusion.

Screeching Swarm absorbs $111600s1 healing and inflicts $111600s2 Shadow damage every $111600t2 sec. The Swarm detaches from its host after $111600d.

The Swarm also inflicts $111644s1 damage every $111643t1 sec. to enemies within $111644A1 yards.
The Maker takes control of a player, causing them to fight their allies for $30923d. The controlled player gains an increased $30923s2% damage done and $30923s3% attack speed.
The Maker throws a beaker at a player, inflicting $40059s1 Nature damage to all players within $40059A1 yards of the target, knocking them up.
Raigonn's Impervious Carapace reduces the damage dealt to Raigonn by $107118s1% until players destroy his Vulnerability.
Raigonn exposes his Vulnerability, allowing players to ride on his head and attack it! Destroying the Vulnerability also destroys Raigonn's Carapace.

Raigonn charges towards the inner door and the impact of the Headbutt inflicts $111671s1 Physical damage to enemies within $111671A1 yards. Impacting the door also throws all enemies on Raigonn's Vulnerability to the ground.
The broken Mantid Carapace increases Raigonn's damage taken by $107146s2%.
Raigonn fixates on a random player for $111723d., and their movement speed increases by $111723s2%.
Raigonn stomps, inflicting $111728s1 Physical damage to all nearby enemies. Each time he stomps, he gains an application of Frenzy, increasing his damage dealt by $111730s1%.
Activating the Cell Door Level opens the 4 Orc prison cells in succession.
Fel Orc Neophytes enter a frenzy, increasing their attack speed by $8269s1% for $8269d.
Fel Orc Neophytes charge a player, inflicting Physical damage.
Fel Orc Neophytes ignore threat, attacking any player that they choose.
Broggok sprays slime, inflicting $30913s1 Nature damage to all players in front of him.
Broggok creates a poison cloud beneath him. The poison cloud grows in size over time and inflicts $38463s1 Nature damage every $38463t1 sec to all players in it.
Broggok shoots poison at a player, inflicting $38459s1 Nature damage and an additional $38459s2 Nature damage every $38459t2 sec for $38459d.

Harlan jumps into the center of the room and begins to spin rapidly with his axe. While spinning, Harlan inflicts  $111215m1% weapon damage as Physical damage to all targets within $111394A1 yards. Harlan carries away targets damaged in this way as he continues spinning around the room.
Harlan inflicts $111217m1% of his normal melee damage to all targets in front of him.
Harlan periodically calls two Scarlet Defenders to come to his aid throughout the encounter.
Scarlet Defenders feature heavy armor to protect them from all damage.

While a Scarlet Defender wears their Heavy Armor, they take $113959m1% less damage until their armor breaks from taking $113959m2 damage. Defenders also take $111323m1% less damage from area effect damage.
Scarlet Defenders who receive sufficient damage lose their Heavy Armor and take $112920m1% additional damage.
Five Shadowmoon Channelers defend Keli'dan the Breaker during his fel ritual.
Shadowmoon Channelers hurl bolts of dark magic at a player, inflicting Shadow damage.
Shadowmoon Channelers mark a player, increasing their Shadow damage taken by $30937s1% for $30937d.
Once all of the Shadowmoon Channelers are defeated, Keli'dan the Breaker cancels his ritual and attacks.
Kelidan the Breaker hurls bolts of dark magic, inflicting $17228s1 Shadow damage to all players within $17228A1 yards.
Keli'dan the Breaker corrupts all players within $30938A1 yards, inflicting $30938s1 Shadow damage every $30938t1 sec for $30938d.

Keli'dan the Breaker banishes himself, making him invulnerable, and begins to cast a Fire Nova. Fire Nova inflicts $33775s1 Fire damage to all players within $33775A1 yards of Keli'dan when he completes his cast.
Keli'dan the Breaker inflicts $37372s1 Shadow damage to a player and their nearby allies, affecting up to $37372x1 targets.
Saboteur Kip'tilak picks a random location in the room and throws a pack of Stable Munitions there.
These explosive materials will not explode unless detonated by another explosion.

When explosions from other Stable Munitions or Sabotage come into contact with Stable Munitions, they explode outward in the four cardinal directions inflicting $107215s1 Fire damage to all players in their path.

Saboteur Kip'tilak attaches four explosives to the back of a random player. When Sabotage expires, the charges explode outward in the four cardinal directions inflicting $107215s1 Fire damage to all players in their path. Sabotage inflicts $113645s2 Fire damage to the victim when the explosion occurs.
When Saboteur Kip'tilak reaches 70% and 30% remaining health, he detonates all explosive charges currently in play.

Flameweaver Kogler tries to light the books ablaze containing the Scarlet Crusade's past. Players may intercept the fiery bolt, which inflicts $113364s2 Fire damage. If Koegler's attack succesfully hits the books, they begin to burn.
The Burning Books inflict $113620s1 Fire damage every $113620t1 sec to enemies within $113620A1 yards for $113616d.

Koegler unleashes a sweeping series of attacks that mimic the deadly fire breath of a Dragon. The Breath inflicts $113653s1 Fire damage, an additional $113653s2 Fire damage every $113653t2 sec., and confuses the target for $113653d.
Flameweaver Koegler casts this preparatory spell, making his next three spells cast nearly instantly.
Flameweaver Koegler unleashes a barrage of Fireballs, inflicting $113691s1 Fire damage to all enemies within $113691A1 yards.
Flameweaver Koegler casts a huge Pyroblast at his current target, inflicting $113690s1 Fire damage, then an additional $113690s2 Fire damage every $113690t2 sec for $113690d.
Commander Sarannis infuses her weapon with Arcane power, granting her melee attacks a chance to increase her target's Arcane damage taken by $34794s1% for $34794d. This effect stacks.
Commander Sarannis unleashes a devastating blow of Arcane damage to her current target.
Commander Sarannis attacks twice.
When Commander Sarannis reaches 55% health, she summons 3 Bloodwarder Reservists and a Bloodwarder Mender.
Bloodwarder Mender blasts a player, inflicting Shadow damage.
Bloodwarder Mender calls upon Holy magic to heal an ally for $35096s1% of their maximum health.
Bloodwarder Mender infuses an ally with Holy energy, increasing their magic damage dealt by $34809s1% for $34809d.
Bloodwarder Reservist strikes a player, inflicting Arcane damage.
When Commander Sarannis reaches 66% and 33% health, she summons 3 Bloodwarder Reservists and a Bloodwarder Mender.
Bloodwarder Mender blasts a player, inflicting Shadow damage.
Bloodwarder Mender calls upon Holy magic to heal an ally for $35096s1% of their maximum health.
Bloodwarder Mender infuses an ally with Holy energy, increasing their magic damage dealt by $34809s1% for $34809d.
Bloodwarder Reservist strikes a player, inflicting Arcane damage.
High Botanist Freywinn plants a seedling every 5 seconds which sprouts into a blue, green, red or white seedling.
Master Snowdrift begins combat by using his fists and feet.
Master Snowdrift harnesses and unleashes his Chi energy at the players.
Master Snowdrift throws a Ball of Fire at the players, inflicting $106470s1 Fire damage to all players in its path.

Title_lang: Stage 3: I Can Do So Much More!
BodyText_lang: Master Snowdrift resorts to his grappling and countering techniques to take down the players.

Master Snowdrift chases down one player at random. If Master Snowdrift catches his target, he performs a Tornado Slam on them.  The Tornado Slam inflicts $106352m1% of the victim's maximum health as Physical damage on the player.
Master Snowdrift momentarily assumes an entirely defensive posture. Any attacks made against Master Snowdrift miss and cause him to retaliate.

While in his Parry Stance, Master Snowdrift counters anyone attacking him in melee range with a Quivering Palm, inflicting $106422s1 Physical damage and stunning them for $106422d. Master Snowdrift then follows up the attack by using Unleash Vibrations.
While in his Parry Stance, Master Snowdrift counters anyone attacking him outside melee range with a Flying Kick, inflicting $106439s2 Physical damage.
Master Snowdrift strikes numerous times with his fists. The impact of his fists inflicts $106854s1 Fire damage on any player in front of Master Snowdrift.
Master Snowdrift continuously spins and kicks out at all players within range. Tornado Kick inflicts $106433s1 Physical damage and knocks back any player within the Tornado.
Blue Seedlings wrap tendrils around the feet of all players within $34782A1 yards every $34781t1 sec, reducing their movement speed by $34782s1% for $34782d.
Green Seedlings inflict $17466s1 Nature damage every $34757t1 seconds to all players within $34758A1 yards.
Red Seedlings blast a player, inflicting $36339s1 Fire damage.
White Seedlings encase a player in a block of ice, stunning them for $34752d.
High Botanist Freywinn transforms into a tree, begins to cast Tranquility, and calls upon 3 Frayer Protectors to defend him.
High Botanist Freywin is immune to all damage for $34551d or until he is no longer defended by Frayer Protectors.
High Botanist Freywin regernates all nearby allies, healing them for $34550s1 every $34550t1 sec for $34550d.
Frayer Protectors fling thorns at a player, inflicting Nature damage.
Thorngrin the Tender teleports a player to his platform, stunning them and draining $34661s3 health every $34661t3 sec for $34661d. Thorngrin heals himself for the amount drained.
Thorngrin the Tender ignites the area surrounding him, inflicting $34660s1 Fire damage to all players within $34660A1 yards every $34659t1 sec for $34659d.
After sacrificing a player, Thorngrin the Tender enrages, increasing his attack speed by $34670s2% and his Physical damage dealt by $34670s1% for $34670d.

Laj diseases a player, increasing their damage taken by $34697s1% and inflicting $34697s2 Nature damage every $34697t2 sec for $34697d. The diseased player has a chance of spreading their illness to their nearest ally.
Laj thrashes at its current target, attacking $3391s1 additional times.
Laj periodically shifts elements, increasing its resistance to that element by $34703s2% and decreasing its resistance to the opposing element by $34703s3%.
Laj increases its resistance to Arcane and decreases its resistance to Shadow.
Laj increases its resistance to Fire and decreases its resistance to Frost.
Laj increases its resistance to Frost and decreases its resistance to Fire.
Laj increases its resistance to Nature and decreases its resistance to Shadow.
Laj increases its resistance to Shadow and decreases its resistance to Arcane and Nature.
Laj teleports to its platform and summons two thorn sprouts to defend it.
Thorn Lashers launch thorns at a random player, inflicting $35072s1 Physical damage every $35071t1 sec for $35071d.
Thorn Flayers inflict Shadow damage to a player every $35507t1 sec for $35507d, reducing their movement speed by $35507s2%.
Warp Splinter inflicts $34716s1 Physical damage to all players within $34716A1 yards, stunning them for $34716d and increasing the Physical damage they take by $34716s3%.
Warp Splinter hurls magical bolts, inflicting $36705s1 Arcane damage to all players within $36705A1 yards.
Warp Splinter raises 6 Saplings to life to aid him in battle. After $34741d, the Saplings will sacrifice themselves, healing Warp Splinter for an amount equal to their remaining health.
Mechano-Lord Capacitus reduces a player's Stamina by $35161s1 for $35161d.
Mechano-Lord Capacitus frequently summons Nether Charges which detonate after 15 seconds, inflicting $35152s1 Arcane damage to all players within $35152A1 yards.
Mechano-Lord Capacitus surrounds himself in a protective shield that reflects $35158s1% of all harmful spells for $35158d.
Mechano-Lord Capacitus surrounds himself with a protective shield that inflicts $35159s1 Arcane damage to melee attackers when hit.

Mechano-Lord Capacitus charges all players with energy, shifting their polarity to either positive or negative. Damage done by the player will be increased for each similarly charged player that is within $39093A1 yards and they will inflict Nature damage to all oppositely charged players within $39093A1 yards every $39091t2 seconds.
Nethermancer Sepethrea inflicts Fire damage to all players in front of her, disorienting them for $35250d.
Nethermancer Sepethrea's weapon is enchanted with Frost, giving her successful melee attacks a chance to inflict Frost damage and slow the movement speed of her target for $35263d.
Nethermancer Sepethrea blasts a player with magic, inflicting Arcane damage and knocking them back, reducing their total threat by half.
Nethermancer Sepethrea summons 2 Raging Flames when she enters combat. Raging Flames ignore threat and pursue a player for a short time.

Raging Flames surround themselves with an inferno for $39346d, inflicting Fire damage to all players within $35283A1 yards every second. While aflame, Raging Flames are unable to move or use abilities. When the inferno ends, Raging Flames choose a new target to pursue.
Pathaleon the Calculator takes control of a player, forcing them to attack their allies for $35280d.
Pathaleon the Calculator rages, increasing his attack speed by $35289s2% and his Physical damage by $35289s1 for $35289d.
Pathaleon the Calculator drains $36021s1 mana from a player, charging himself with Arcane energy for $36021d. This effect stacks up to $36021u times.
Pathaleon the Calculator silences all players within $36022A1 yards for $36022d. In addition, he gains Mana for each Mana Tap charge he currently has.
Pathaleon the Calculator sends out a blast wave of magic, inflicting Arcane damage to all players within $15453A1 yards.
Pathaleon the Calculator summons 3 Nether Wraiths to aid him in battle.
Nether Wraiths hurl magical bolts at a player, inflicting Arcane damage.
Grand Warlock Nethekurse inflicts Shadow damage to a player and their nearest allies, affecting up to $30495x1 targets.
Grand Warlock Nethekurse causes a player to cower in horror for $30500d, inflicting $30500s1 Shadow damage. Nethekurse gains 100% of the damage caused in health.
Grand Warlock Nethekurse creates a fissure of Consumption under a player, inflicting $30498s1 Shadow damage every $30498t1 sec while they are inside of the fissure.

When Grand Warlock Nethekurse reaches 25% health, he enters a Dark Spin of shadow and steel. Dark Spin inflicts Physical damage to all players within $30508A1 yards and hurls bolts of dark magic every $30502t1 sec that inflict $30505s1 Shadow damage to a random player.
Liu Flameheart rapidly assaults players with three Serpent martial arts attacks.
When Liu Flameheart reaches 70% remaining health, she channels the essence of the Jade Serpent to aid her in battle. Each of her attacks now has an additional effect.
When Liu Flameheart reaches 30% remaining health, she enters a trance, making herself invulnerable and summoning the spirit of Yu'lon to defend her in battle.
Instructor Chillheart summons a wall of ice that slowly sweeps across the room, instantly killing any player it touches.
Instructor Chillheart shatters the soul of a player, inflicting $111631s1 Shadow damage every second for $111631d. When Wrack Soul expires, it jumps to another player.
Instructor Chillheart's icy touch causes her next 10 melee attacks to inflict an additional $111224s1 Frost damage.
Instructor Chillheart summons ice at a player's location that explodes from the ground, inflicting $114886s1 Frost damage to all nearby players.

When Instructor Chillheart's physical body dies, the foul magic that animated her escapes back to her phylactery.

Fragments of Instructor Chillheart's soul escape the phylactery and animate the tomes of magic scattered throughout the classroom.
The Anarchist Arcanist creates an orb of magic that explodes on impact, inflicting $113859s1 Arcane damage to all players within $113859A1 yards.

Title_lang: Antonidas' Self Help Guide to Standing in Fire

BodyText_lang: Antonidas' Self Help Guide to Standing in Fire inflicts $120027s1 Fire damage to all players within $120027A1 yards of it.

Title_lang: Wander's Colossal Book of Shadow Puppets

BodyText_lang: Wander's Colossal Book of Shadow Puppets hurls bolts of dark magic at random players, inflicting $113809s1 Shadow damage.
Jandice rears her staff back with a flash of wondrous Arcane force, unleashing a barrage of attacks that inflict $114061s1 Arcane damage in a cone in front of her.
Jandice creates a gravity distortion field that inflicts $114038s2 Shadow damage to all enemies who enter it, knocking them back and causing them to briefly go blind.

At 66% and 33% health Jandice dissipates into thin air, creating multiple illusions of herself. Destroying the one illusion Jandice hides behind forces her back into the fray.$[!2,4

In Heroic difficulty, defeating the wrong image causes a Flash Bang, inflicting $113866s1 Arcane damage to all enemies.$]
Jandice hides amongst multiple illusions of herself, dancing in a Whirl of Illusion that inflicts $113775s1 Arcane damage to all enemies every $114048t1 second.
A young Yaungol faces his own Strife and Peril. He must find a balance between the two to set his soul free.

Title_lang: The Champion of the Five Suns
BodyText_lang: In the days of old, five suns burned brightly in the sky. Great fires would sweep through the lands of Pandaria until the day that Zao Sunseeker shot a defiant arrow into the sky, bringing down 4 of the 5 suns.
The intense heat of a sun burns a random player for$107223s1 Fire damage.
The Haunting Sha gazes into their victim's soul, inflicting $114646s1 Shadow damage.
The Haunting Sha have now possessed Zao Sunseeker. You must now defeat him to cleanse his corruption.
Zao shoots madly at his perceived enemies, inflicting $113017s1 Fire damage to random enemies.
Instructor Chillheart wreaths a player in ice for $111610d, causing them to inflict $111616s1 Frost damage to all of their allies within $111616A1 yards every second.

Rattlegore's dull blades rust with each successful melee attack, increasing damage by $113765s1% but lowering attack speed by $113765s2% and movement speed by $113765s3% for $113765d.  This effect stacks.
Rattlegore launches a powerful spike of bone at a random player, inflicting $113999s1 Physical damage and knocking them back a great distance. Bone Armor absorbs the effect of Bone Spikes.

The souls of the dead Boneweavers continue to torment the living, periodically engulfing a section of the room in Soulflame. The flame inflicts $114009s1 Fire damage every $114007t1 sec. and grows in size over time.

Title_lang: Stage One: Fetch Me Their Bones!
BodyText_lang: Darkmaster Gandling turns Lilian Voss against her former allies, employing her powerful abilities to gather more corpses for his devious purposes. Though she tries to fight against his dark will, she cannot control her actions at this time.
Bone Piles lie scattered throughout the summoning room. Interacting with a Bone Pile grants a player a charge of Bone Armor.
Surrounds the caster with a series of whirling bones that absorbs one Bone spell.
Lilian leaps onto a player and strikes them with both runeblades, inflicting $111775s1 Shadow damage to players within $111775A1 yards.
Lilian draws upon dark powers to pull all players to her location.

Title_lang: Stage Two: Your Soul is Mine!
BodyText_lang: When Lilian's health reaches 60%, her will finally breaks. Darkmaster Gandling forcefully rips her anguished soul from her physical body, then commands Lilian's Soul to attack the players.
Lilian's soul blazes with barely-contained hatred, periodically inflicting $111642s1 Fire damage to all players.

Lilian's anguish is further unleashed when striking players in melee. For every melee strike, Lilian will unleash another barrage of Blazing Soul. However, the movement speed of Lilian's Soul is significantly reduced.

Title_lang: Stage Three: A Perfectly Good Corpse
BodyText_lang:
When Lilian's Soul reaches 1% health, Lilian's Soul fades into the spirit realm and cannot be attacked.

Darkmaster Gandling reanimates what remains of Lilian's physical body to fight alongside Lilian's Soul.

The reanimated corpse retains all abilities Lilian Voss used in Stage One.
Periodically summons a patch of dark fire at the player's location, inflicting $111628s1 Fire damage every $111587t2 seconds.
Lilian's Soul fixates on a player. She will only attempt to attack that player and cannot be taunted.
When Lilian's physical body reaches 1% remaining health, she musters the strength to recombine with her soul for a final assault on Darkmaster Gandling.

At 90%, 60%, and 30% health remaining, Ook-Ook goes bananas! This increases his attack speed by $106651s1% and damage dealt by $106651s2%.  Stacks up to $106651U times.

In addition, this causes a wave of Rolling Barrels.
Ook-Ook pounds the ground every $106807t1 sec. for $106807d, inflicting $106808s1 Physical damage to all enemies within a 45-degree cone and stunning them for $106808d.

Ook-Ook's entourage periodically throw Rolling Barrels, which roll across the room until they hit a wall, player, or Ook-Ook himself.  At 90%, 60% and 30% health remaining, the entourage throws more barrels.

Rolling Barrels inflict $106648s1 Physical damage to players on contact. If a player rides a barrel into Ook-Ook, they inflict $106784s2 Physical damage and increase damage taken by $106648s2% for $106648d. This effect stacks.
Hoptallus slowly turns in a circle spewing vile carrot juices. The juices inflict $112945s1 Physical damage and knock back any targets within a 20-degree cone in front of Hoptallus.
Hoptallus spins in a rapid circle. Inflicts $112993s1 damage every $112992t1 sec. to surrounding units, but slows movement speed by $112992s2%.
The tiniest virmen, Hoplings do little more than hop around and bite things!
If there are no players near Yan-Zhu, he will begin casting Brew Bolts. Inflicts $114548s1 Frost damage and increases magic damage taken by the target by $114548s2% for $114548d. This effect stacks.
Uncle Gao's new fermentation procedures grant Yan-Zhu one of two ale brew abilities.
Uncle Gao has modified the family recipe, granting Yan-Zhu one of two stout brew abilities.
Brother Korloff begins to unleash a flurry of fiery blows, inflicting $114808s1% of his normal melee damage as Fire damage to targets in front of him every $114807t1 sec. for $114807d.
Brother Korloff flies towards a random player and performs a Firestorm Kick, inflicting $113766s1 Fire damage to all players within $113766A1 yards.
Whenever Brother Korloff loses 10% of his total health, a Rising Flame burns within him and he inflicts $114410s1% additional Fire damage. This effect stacks.
At 50% remaining health Brother Korloff burns brightly enough to leave a trail of fire as he moves. The Scorched Earth inflicts $114465s1 Fire damage every $99128t1 sec.
Houndmaster Braun throws one of his knives at a random enemy, inflicting $114020s1 Physical damage and applying Bloody Mess to all enemies in the knife's path.

Houndmaster Braun leaps onto a random enemy and whirls around, releasing a spray of knives at all targets within $114242A2 yards, inflicting $114242s2 Physical damage and applying Bloody Mess to the target and any of its nearby allies.
Houndmaster Braun calls for an Obedient Hound to enter the fight at 90%, 80%, 70%, and 60% remaining health.
Trained by Houndmaster Braun, this large mastiff follows any order given to it by his master.
At 50% remaining health and unable to control his dogs, Houndmaster Braun begins to attack $116140s2% faster and inflicts $116140m3% more damage.

Title_lang: Stage One: Still Waters, Rise Up!
BodyText_lang: Wise Mari shields himself and uses the corrupt waters of the fountain to assault players.

At Wise Mari's orders, the sha-corrupted waters of the fountain coalesce into a Corrupt Living Water Elemental.

Defeating a Corrupt Living Water Elemental removes one layer of Water Bubble and causes it to split into three Corrupt Droplets.

Title_lang: Stage Two: Behold the Torrential Waters!
BodyText_lang: After defeating four Corrupt Living Waters, Wise Mari unleashes all of his remaining power.

Title_lang: Stage One: Let Me Show You My Power!
BodyText_lang: Gu Cloudstrike calls for the Azure Serpent to help him defeat the intruders.

Title_lang: Stage Two: Charge Me With Your Power!
BodyText_lang: Gu Cloudstrike enters a meditative state, becoming immune to all damage. The Azure Serpent moves in to attack.

Title_lang: Stage Three: Do Not Fail Me!
BodyText_lang: After the players defeat the Azure Serpent, Gu Cloudstrike rejoins the fight.
Gu Cloudstrike inflicts $106984s1 Nature damage to a random player, inflicting an additional $107202s1 Nature damage to all players within $107202A1 yards of the target.

The Azure Serpent creates a Static Field at the location of a random player, inflicting $106932s1 Nature damage to all players within $106932a1 yards of the point of impact. The Static Field then persists for $106941d, inflicting an additional $128889s1 Nature damage every $106941t1 sec.
The Azure Serpent shields Gu Cloudstrike, making him immune to all damage.
The Azure Serpent unleashes Lightning Breath within a 45 degree cone in front of him, inflicting $102572s1 Nature damage every $102573t1 sec. for $102573d.

The Azure Serpent casts a Magnetic Shroud onto every player. The Shroud absorbs $107140s1 healing cast on each player and inflicts $107140s2 Nature damage every $107140t2 sec. The Shroud overloads when healing on a player exceeds its capacity, removing the Magnetic Shroud. The overload then heals all other players within $107174A1 yards for $107174s1 healing divided by the number of players within range.
Periodically inflicts Nature damage to nearby enemies, frequency proportional to missing health.
The new military commander of the Scarlet Crusade attacks the players with a series of lightning quick strikes.
Commander Durand rapidly shifts around the battlefield, attacking random players and inflicting $115629s2 Physical damage every time he strikes.
Commander Durand quickly dashes through his enemies to a location, inflicting $115739s1 Physical damage to every enemy in his path.
The High Inquisitor of the Scarlet Crusade comes to the aid of Commander Durand when he falls, resurrecting him to fight at her side.
High Inquisitor Whitemane wraps an ally in a magical shield that absorbs $22187s1 damage.
High Inquisitor Whitemane smites her current target, inflicting $114848s1 Holy damage.
High Inquisitor Whitemane resurrects all fallen Scarlet Judicators within 100 yards to come to her aid.
Striker Ga'dok charges a nearby enemy and devours them, inflicting $106933s1 Physical damage every $106933t1 sec. for $106933d.
Striker Ga'dok impales his current target, inflicting $107047s1% of their total health as Physical damage.
Hoptallus will periodically emit a shrill cry, calling for aid from Hoplings, Hoppers, and Boppers.
The larger Hoppers carry a barrel of explosive brew in their mouths.
If a Hopper reaches its target, it hops madly then explodes. The explosion inflicts $114291s1 Fire damage to players within $114291A1 yards and knocks them down.
The large Boppers carry a heavy hammer.
When Boppers die, they drop their Big Ol' Hammers. Players can pick up the Hammer to gain three charges of the Smash! ability.
Slam the Big Ol' Hammer into the ground and knock up all nearby virmen, destroying all Hoppers and Hoplings within $111666A1 yards and dealing heavy damage to Boppers.
Uncle Gao's crazy experiments grant Yan-Zhu one of two wheat brew abilities.

Yan-Zhu infuses a random player with an excessive quantity of brew. This Bloat causes brew to gush from their ears for $106546d, inflicting $106560s1 Frost damage and knocking back targets in a 10-degree cone on either side of the bloated player.

The heavy Blackout Brew inflicts $106851s1 Frost damage to all players and applies 3 stacks of Blackout Brew. Stacks can be removed by moving and jumping. If Blackout Brew reaches 10 stacks, the Brew stuns the player for $106857d.
Yan-Zhu covers himself with 8 small bubbles. Each bubble grants Yan-Zhu 10% damage reduction. This effect stacks.
Yan-Zhu summons forth Yeasty Brew Alementals to aid him.

The Yeasty Brew Alemental fires a fermentation beam towards Yan-Zhu the Uncasked, but players may intercept the beam and receive its effect by standing between the two Alementals. The fermentation restores $114451s1% of health and mana every 1 sec. to the affected target.

Yan-Zhu fills the room with Carbonation for $115003d. The Carbonation inflicts $114386s1 Frost damage every $115003t1 sec. to enemies that are close to the ground and prevents them from attacking or casting spells due to acute asphyxiation.

In addition, Carbonation causes Fizzy Bubbles to spawn.
Clicking on a Fizzy Bubble grants a player the ability to fly for $114459d.
Yan-Zhu periodically summons forth walls of sudsy brew. The onrushing brew inflicts $114466s1 Frost damage every $114467t1 seconds to players that stand within the wall and stuns them for $114466d.
The sudsy nature of Yan-Zhu grants players the ability to jump extra high.
When Striker Ga'dok reaches 70% and 30% remaining health, he strafes the platform with fire bombs. The resulting flames inflict $116297s1 Fire damage every $116298t1 sec. to enemies caught within it.
These flying Mantid continuously bombard the platform with Acid Bombs.

Mantid Disruptors periodically bombard the location of a random player with an acid bomb, inflicting $115458s1 Nature damage every $115457t1 sec. to players standing within the $115458A1 yard radius impact area.
Mantid Strikers attack players on the platform during Striker Ga'dok's strafe runs.

Commander Ri'mok periodically exudes a $107091A1 yard radius area of viscous fluid at his location. Contact with the fluid increases Ri'mok's damage by $107091s1% and reduces damage dealt by players standing in it by $107122s1% every $107088t1 sec. This effect stacks five times.
